The paper deals with algorithms for solving the weighted discrete $p$-center problem for tree networks, which involves finding the optimal location of $p$ centers in a network to minimize the maximum distance between a node and its closest center. This problem is a classic problem in computer science and falls under the category of computational geometry (cs.CG) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The algorithms proposed in the paper involve data structures and optimization techniques, which are typical topics in the sub-category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the theoretical analysis of the algorithms, which involves mathematical optimization and numerical analysis, making it relevant to the sub-categories of game theory (cs.GT) and numerical analysis (cs.NA).
